minor Propoſition, 1. That the reaſon why Faith is neceſſary in perſons, who have not been baptized in their infancy, to render them capapble of Baptiſm, is becauſe it is that mean, by which thoſe that are to admit unto baptiſm, come to know that they are in the love of God; and that if ſuch a thing could be known without ſuch a profeſſion of Faith, as it may in the caſe of Infants, then ſuch a profeſſion would not be neceſſary in order to ſuch an admiſſion;
